Non-U.S. dollar foreign exchange risk
Non-U.S. dollar FX risk is the risk that changes in foreign exchange
rates affect the value of the Firm’s assets or liabilities or future results.
The Firm has structural non-U.S. dollar FX exposures arising from
capital investments, forecasted expense and revenue, the investment
securities portfolio and non-U.S. dollar-denominated debt issuance. Treasury and
CIO, working in partnership with the lines of business, primarily
manage these risks on behalf of the Firm. Treasury and CIO may
hedge certain of these risks using derivatives within risk limits
governed by the CTC Risk Committee.
