Valuation adjustments on fair value option elected liabilities
The valuation of the Firm’s liabilities for which the fair value option
has been elected requires consideration of the Firm’s own credit risk.
DVA on fair value option elected liabilities reflects changes
(subsequent to the issuance of the liability) in the Firm’s probability of
default and LGD, which are estimated based on changes in the Firm’s
credit spread observed in the bond market. Realized (gains)/losses due
to DVA for fair value option elected liabilities are reported in principal
transactions revenue. Unrealized (gains)/losses are reported in OCI.
Refer to page 174 in this Note and Note 23 for further information.
