Deferred taxes
Deferred income tax expense/(benefit) results from differences
between assets and liabilities measured for financial reporting purposes
versus income tax return purposes. Deferred tax assets are recognized
if, in management’s judgment, their realizability is determined to be
more likely than not. If a deferred tax asset is determined to be
unrealizable, a valuation allowance is established. The significant
components of deferred tax assets and liabilities are reflected in the
following table as of December 31, 2018 and 2017.
